    "# Example 3 {background-color=\"#1a5276\"}\n",
    "\n",
    "## Euler Equation: $t^2x''-2tx'+2x=t^3\\sin t$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Variable-coefficient** homogeneous part — Euler–Cauchy equation.\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "**Standard form** (divide by $t^2$): $x''-\\frac{2}{t}x'+\\frac{2}{t^2}x = t\\sin t$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Homogeneous solutions**: try $x=t^r$:\n",
    "$$r(r-1)-2r+2 = r^2-3r+2=(r-1)(r-2)=0 \\;\\Rightarrow\\; r=1,2$$\n",
    "$$x_1=t, \\quad x_2=t^2, \\quad W = t\\cdot 2t - t^2\\cdot 1 = t^2$$\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "$$u_1' = -\\frac{t^2\\cdot t\\sin t}{t^2} = -t\\sin t \\;\\Rightarrow\\; u_1 = t\\cos t-\\sin t$$\n",
    "$$u_2' = \\frac{t\\cdot t\\sin t}{t^2} = \\sin t \\;\\Rightarrow\\; u_2 = -\\cos t$$\n",
    "\n",
    ". . .\n",
    "\n",
    "$$x_p = t(t\\cos t-\\sin t)+t^2(-\\cos t) = t^2\\cos t - t\\sin t - t^2\\cos t = -t\\sin t$$\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\boxed{x(t) = C_1 t + C_2 t^2 - t\\sin t}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "## Example 3 — Solution Plot"
